The paper deals with information theoretic bounds for low-rank tensor completion, which is a problem in information theory and machine learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and statistical learning, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's focus on tensor completion and its mathematical derivations suggest that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
